<HEADLINE>
DEPARTMENT STORES APRIL SALES UP 2.35% OVER LAST YEAR: MOEA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 28 (CNA) 05/28/07  21:31:28 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The business turnover of local department stores in April reached
NT$16.8 billion (US$506 million), marking a 2.35 percent hike
over last April and an 18.41 percent increase over the previous
month, a Ministry of Economic Affairs (MOEA) official said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Quoting statistics recently released by the MOEA, the official
said the accumulated turnover of department stores from January
to April this year was NT$68.7 billion, up 4.75 percent year-on-
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the increase was the outcome of
promotions in the run-up to Mother's Day, which fell on May 13
this year.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales of general merchandise in April was NT$59.2 billion,
an increase of 1.42 percent over last April, while accumulated
sales from January to April this year was NT$246.9 billion, 4.34
percent higher than the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Among the general merchandise retail sales, supermarket turnover
in April was NT$7.2 billion, an increase of 6.26 percent over
last year, and business turnover for the first four months was
7.76 percent higher than last year's.
</P>
<P>
April sales of convenience chain stores was NT$15.8 billion, an
increase of 1.8 percent over last April, while turnover for the
first four months was 3.78 percent higher year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, business turnover of retail outlets in April was
NT$10.7 billion, down by 3.06 percent from last April, while
accumulated sales from January to April increased 2.41 percent
over the same period of last year.
</P>
